   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3183_1b.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>The Little Orchard</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Shoreham</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Kent</addrLine>
               </address>


               <dateline>
                  <date when="1915-05-23">May 23./15</date>
               </dateline>

               <note hand="unknown" rend="pencil" style="transform:rotateZ(-90deg)">
                  <hi rend="underline">Hon. Mrs Henniker</hi>
               </note>

               <salute>My dear friend:</salute>
            </opener>


            <p> I know you will help me &amp; my dear faithful old <persName
                  ref="#ps:AnnaHirschmann">Anna</persName> – Will you very kindly say that you have
               known <persName ref="#ps:AnnaHirschmann"><hi rend="underline">Anna</hi>
                  <hi rend="underline">Hirschmann</hi></persName> for a considerable time, &amp;
               that you believe her to be a most devoted honest, loyal person – (or any words you
               like to use?) who may <hi rend="underline">safely be allowed to remain in <placeName
                     ref="#pl:England"><hi rend="underline">England</hi></placeName></hi>. I want to
               attach <hi rend="underline">your</hi> testimonial to a form that has to go to the
                  <placeName ref="#pl:HomeOffice">Home Office</placeName>, to enable her to stay
               with me.</p>

            <p> She is not strong, &amp; it <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan></choice> simply break her heart to leave me.</p>

            <p> Y<hi rend="underline">our</hi> name <choice><abbr>w<hi rend="superscript"
                     >d</hi></abbr>
                  <expan>would</expan></choice> be a help to her &amp; to me.</p>

            <closer>
               <salute>Ever <choice><abbr>yr</abbr>
                     <expan>your</expan></choice>
                  <choice><abbr>aff.</abbr>
                     <expan>affectionate</expan></choice> friend</salute>
               <signed>FloH.</signed>

            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p> I enclose cover to save you trouble.</p>
               <p> Will you very kindly <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3183_2b.jpg"/> write the
                  statement <hi rend="underline">not</hi> as a letter to <hi rend="underline"
                     >me</hi> – but formally beginning "I am glad to vouch for" – or I am glad to
                  state" – re –</p>
            </postscript>


         </div>
      </body>
